{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HwUi2mZprC3V8CvJWnRFd2","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c50fb69-0476-4a5d-8998-78fcdfa47c24","uuid":"be47e058-ea4e-46ea-879c-e854ac6ef50f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:11:16.748Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 5)\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":22,"newStart":1,"newLines":1,"lines":["-# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 4)","-","-### 8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation — create-story (2026-03-23T11:35Z)","-","-- **Bug found in existing code:** `configureAgent()` falls through to set `agent_sdk: 'traceloop'` for Rust projects — no Rust Traceloop SDK exists. Story task 4 fixes this.","-- **Scope expansion:** AC2 requires writing `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` to `.env.codeharness` — current code only writes `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME` there. Necessary for Rust apps that read env vars directly.","-- **Risk: otlp.ts at 375 lines**, will grow to ~410 (exceeds 300-line NFR1 limit). Pre-existing violation.","-- **Risk: AC8 integration-required** — needs real Rust toolchain + `cargo` for full pipeline verification.","-","-### 8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation — dev-story (2026-03-23T11:50Z)","-","-- **Pre-existing test failures:** 6 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts` and `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts`. Unrelated to story 8-7. May have broken between 8-6 and now.","-- **Mock isolation quirk:** `installRustOtlp` test needed explicit `mockClear()` because `vi.restoreAllMocks()` in `beforeEach` doesn't fully clear `mock.calls` on module-level `vi.mock`'d functions. Minor fragility.","-- **File line count:** `otlp.ts` is now ~423 lines, exceeding the 300-line NFR1 limit. `ensureEndpointEnvVar` duplicates pattern from `ensureServiceNameEnvVar` — could be consolidated.","-- **Sprint-status.yaml corruption:** The dev-story agent overwrote sprint-status.yaml with placeholder content. Had to restore from git and manually set status to `review`.","-","-### 8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation — code-review (2026-03-23T12:00Z)","-","-- **HIGH: Transport/port mismatch in `templates/otlp/rust.md`** — Template used `.with_tonic()` (gRPC, port 4317) while env var writes `http://localhost:4318` (HTTP). Would fail at runtime. Fixed by changing to `.with_http()`.","-- **MEDIUM: Missing OTEL exporter env vars in `templates/otlp/rust.md`** — Template omitted `OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER`, `OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER`, `OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER`. Fixed.","-- **MEDIUM: `ensureEndpointEnvVar` had two uncovered branches** — \"update existing\" and \"create new file\" paths never directly tested. Fixed by adding 4 unit tests.","-- **LOW (not fixed): Code duplication between `ensureServiceNameEnvVar` and `ensureEndpointEnvVar`** — Could be refactored to a generic `ensureEnvVar()` helper.","+# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 5)"]}],"originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 4)\n\n### 8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation — create-story (2026-03-23T11:35Z)\n\n- **Bug found in existing code:** `configureAgent()` falls through to set `agent_sdk: 'traceloop'` for Rust projects — no Rust Traceloop SDK exists. Story task 4 fixes this.\n- **Scope expansion:** AC2 requires writing `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` to `.env.codeharness` — current code only writes `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME` there. Necessary for Rust apps that read env vars directly.\n- **Risk: otlp.ts at 375 lines**, will grow to ~410 (exceeds 300-line NFR1 limit). Pre-existing violation.\n- **Risk: AC8 integration-required** — needs real Rust toolchain + `cargo` for full pipeline verification.\n\n### 8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation — dev-story (2026-03-23T11:50Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing test failures:** 6 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts` and `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts`. Unrelated to story 8-7. May have broken between 8-6 and now.\n- **Mock isolation quirk:** `installRustOtlp` test needed explicit `mockClear()` because `vi.restoreAllMocks()` in `beforeEach` doesn't fully clear `mock.calls` on module-level `vi.mock`'d functions. Minor fragility.\n- **File line count:** `otlp.ts` is now ~423 lines, exceeding the 300-line NFR1 limit. `ensureEndpointEnvVar` duplicates pattern from `ensureServiceNameEnvVar` — could be consolidated.\n- **Sprint-status.yaml corruption:** The dev-story agent overwrote sprint-status.yaml with placeholder content. Had to restore from git and manually set status to `review`.\n\n### 8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation — code-review (2026-03-23T12:00Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Transport/port mismatch in `templates/otlp/rust.md`** — Template used `.with_tonic()` (gRPC, port 4317) while env var writes `http://localhost:4318` (HTTP). Would fail at runtime. Fixed by changing to `.with_http()`.\n- **MEDIUM: Missing OTEL exporter env vars in `templates/otlp/rust.md`** — Template omitted `OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER`, `OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER`, `OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER`. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: `ensureEndpointEnvVar` had two uncovered branches** — \"update existing\" and \"create new file\" paths never directly tested. Fixed by adding 4 unit tests.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Code duplication between `ensureServiceNameEnvVar` and `ensureEndpointEnvVar`** — Could be refactored to a generic `ensureEnvVar()` helper.\n"}}
