{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HfhqZwWwh6TWP2XDQJjp66","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 8.8: Rust Documentation Scaffolding\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a developer initializing codeharness on a Rust project,\n    10→I want AGENTS.md to include Rust-specific build/test commands and `getProjectName()` to read from Cargo.toml,\n    11→so that AI agents know how to build and test my project and the project name is correct for Rust projects.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. **AC1:** Given a Rust project, when `getStackLabel()` is called, then it returns `'Rust (Cargo.toml)'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. **AC2:** Given a Rust project, when `getCoverageTool()` is called, then it returns `'cargo-tarpaulin'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. **AC3:** Given a Rust project, when `generateAgentsMdContent()` is called, then output includes `cargo build`, `cargo test`, `cargo tarpaulin --out json` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→4. **AC4:** Given a Rust project with `[package]\\nname = \"myapp\"` in Cargo.toml and no package.json, when `getProjectName()` is called, then it returns `'myapp'` (reads from Cargo.toml, not package.json) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→5. **AC5:** Given a Rust project with BOTH `package.json` (name: \"npm-name\") and `Cargo.toml` (name = \"rust-name\"), when `getProjectName()` is called, then it returns `'npm-name'` (package.json takes precedence — existing behavior preserved) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→6. **AC6:** Given a Rust project with a Cargo.toml that has `name` fields in `[dependencies]` but not in `[package]`, when `getProjectName()` is called, then it does NOT return a dependency name — it falls back to `basename(projectDir)` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→7. **AC7:** Given all changes, when `npm test` runs, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions and new Rust docs-scaffold tests pass <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→\n    23→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    24→\n    25→- [x] Task 1: Add Cargo.toml parsing to `getProjectName()` in `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` (AC: #4, #5, #6)\n    26→  - [x] 1.1 After the existing `package.json` check (L19-26), add a Cargo.toml check: if no package.json name found, try reading `Cargo.toml`\n    27→  - [x] 1.2 Parse the `[package]` section to extract `name = \"value\"` using regex `/^\\[package\\][\\s\\S]*?^name\\s*=\\s*\"([^\"]+)\"/m` or equivalent line-by-line parsing\n    28→  - [x] 1.3 IMPORTANT: Only match `name` within the `[package]` section, NOT within `[dependencies]` or other sections — stop at the next `[section]` header\n    29→  - [x] 1.4 If `package.json` exists and has a name, it takes precedence (existing behavior, do not change)\n    30→  - [x] 1.5 If Cargo.toml parse fails or has no `[package]` name, fall through to `basename(projectDir)` as before\n    31→- [x] Task 2: Verify existing Rust branches in `getStackLabel()`, `getCoverageTool()`, `generateAgentsMdContent()` are correct (AC: #1, #2, #3)\n    32→  - [x] 2.1 Confirm `getStackLabel('rust')` already returns `'Rust (Cargo.toml)'` — no change needed\n    33→  - [x] 2.2 Confirm `getCoverageTool('rust')` already returns `'cargo-tarpaulin'` — no change needed\n    34→  - [x] 2.3 Confirm `generateAgentsMdContent(dir, 'rust')` already includes `cargo build`, `cargo test`, `cargo tarpaulin --out json` — no change needed\n    35→- [x] Task 3: Add test cases to `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` (AC: #4, #5, #6, #7)\n    36→  - [x] 3.1 Test: `getProjectName()` with Cargo.toml `[package]\\nname = \"myapp\"` and no package.json returns `'myapp'`\n    37→  - [x] 3.2 Test: `getProjectName()` with BOTH package.json and Cargo.toml returns the package.json name (precedence)\n    38→  - [x] 3.3 Test: `getProjectName()` with Cargo.toml that only has `name` in `[dependencies]` section falls back to basename\n    39→  - [x] 3.4 Test: `getProjectName()` with malformed Cargo.toml falls back to basename\n    40→  - [x] 3.5 Verify existing Rust tests for `getStackLabel`, `getCoverageTool`, `generateAgentsMdContent` still pass\n    41→- [x] Task 4: Run full test suite — zero regressions (AC: #7)\n    42→\n    43→## Dev Notes\n    44→\n    45→### CRITICAL: Most ACs Are Already Implemented\n    46→\n    47→ACs 1, 2, and 3 were implemented in earlier stories (8-1 through 8-6). The code already exists in `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts`:\n    48→\n    49→- **Line 35**: `if (stack === 'rust') return 'Rust (Cargo.toml)';` — AC1 done\n    50→- **Line 41**: `if (stack === 'rust') return 'cargo-tarpaulin';` — AC2 done\n    51→- **Lines 75-82**: Rust branch in `generateAgentsMdContent()` with `cargo build`, `cargo test`, `cargo tarpaulin --out json` — AC3 done\n    52→\n    53→Tests also exist in `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts`:\n    54→- Lines 75-78: `getStackLabel('rust')` test\n    55→- Lines 93-95: `getCoverageTool('rust')` test\n    56→- Lines 121-131: `generateAgentsMdContent` Rust tests\n    57→\n    58→**The only new work is AC4** — adding Cargo.toml parsing to `getProjectName()`. ACs 5 and 6 are edge-case guardrails for AC4. AC7 is regression testing.\n    59→\n    60→### getProjectName() Current Implementation\n    61→\n    62→```typescript\n    63→export function getProjectName(projectDir: string): string {\n    64→  try {\n    65→    const pkgPath = join(projectDir, 'package.json');\n    66→    if (existsSync(pkgPath)) {\n    67→      const pkg = JSON.parse(readFileSync(pkgPath, 'utf-8'));\n    68→      if (pkg.name && typeof pkg.name === 'string') {\n    69→        return pkg.name;\n    70→      }\n    71→    }\n    72→  } catch {\n    73→    // Fall through to basename\n    74→  }\n    75→  return basename(projectDir);\n    76→}\n    77→```\n    78→\n    79→Add a Cargo.toml fallback AFTER the package.json check but BEFORE the `basename` return. The function should try Cargo.toml only if package.json didn't yield a name.\n    80→\n    81→### Cargo.toml Parsing Strategy\n    82→\n    83→Do NOT add a TOML parser dependency (NFR3: no new npm dependencies). Use simple string parsing:\n    84→\n    85→1. Read `Cargo.toml` as UTF-8\n    86→2. Find the `[package]` section header\n    87→3. From that point, scan lines until the next `[section]` header or EOF\n    88→4. Within those lines, match `name = \"value\"` or `name = 'value'`\n    89→5. Return the extracted name\n    90→\n    91→Example regex approach:\n    92→```typescript\n    93→const cargoPath = join(projectDir, 'Cargo.toml');\n    94→if (existsSync(cargoPath)) {\n    95→  const content = readFileSync(cargoPath, 'utf-8');\n    96→  const packageMatch = content.match(/\\[package\\]([^[]*)/s);\n    97→  if (packageMatch) {\n    98→    const nameMatch = packageMatch[1].match(/^\\s*name\\s*=\\s*\"([^\"]+)\"/m);\n    99→    if (nameMatch) {\n   100→      return nameMatch[1];\n   101→    }\n   102→  }\n   103→}\n   104→```\n   105→\n   106→The key is `/\\[package\\]([^[]*)/s` which captures everything after `[package]` until the next `[` (next section header). Then within that captured group, find `name = \"value\"`.\n   107→\n   108→### Architecture Constraints\n   109→\n   110→- **NFR3**: No new npm dependencies — use string matching, not a TOML parser\n   111→- **NFR4**: Cargo.toml parsing uses simple string matching (explicitly stated in architecture)\n   112→- **NFR1**: File must stay under 300 lines — `docs-scaffold.ts` is currently 207 lines, adding ~15 lines for Cargo.toml parsing is safe\n   113→- **NFR5**: Follow existing `try/catch` fallthrough pattern in `getProjectName()`\n   114→\n   115→### Test Patterns\n   116→\n   117→Existing tests use:\n   118→- `mkdtempSync` for temp directories\n   119→- `writeFileSync` to create test files\n   120→- Direct function calls with assertions\n   121→- `vi.mock` for `generateFile` and `readmeTemplate`\n   122→\n   123→For Cargo.toml tests, create a temp directory, write a `Cargo.toml` file with the appropriate content, and call `getProjectName()`.\n   124→\n   125→### Project Structure Notes\n   126→\n   127→Files to modify:\n   128→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Add Cargo.toml parsing to `getProjectName()` (~10-15 lines)\n   129→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — Add Rust project name tests (~30 lines)\n   130→\n   131→Files for reference only (do NOT modify):\n   132→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — Calls `scaffoldDocs()`, no changes needed\n   133→- `src/commands/init.ts` — CLI entry point, no changes needed\n   134→\n   135→### Do NOT Create or Modify\n   136→\n   137→- Do NOT modify `getStackLabel()` — Rust branch already exists\n   138→- Do NOT modify `getCoverageTool()` — Rust branch already exists\n   139→- Do NOT modify `generateAgentsMdContent()` — Rust branch already exists\n   140→- Do NOT create Semgrep rules (that's story 8-9)\n   141→- Do NOT modify OTLP code (that's story 8-7, done)\n   142→- Do NOT add `cargo clippy` or `cargo fmt` to AGENTS.md — the epic AC only requires `cargo build`, `cargo test`, `cargo tarpaulin --out json`\n   143→\n   144→### References\n   145→\n   146→- [Source: src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts — complete docs-scaffold module, 207 lines]\n   147→- [Source: src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts — existing test suite, 195 lines]\n   148→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-rust-stack-support.md#Story8-8 — epic definition]\n   149→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/tech-spec-rust-stack-support.md — tech spec]\n   150→\n   151→### Previous Story Intelligence (8-7)\n   152→\n   153→- 8-7 added `installRustOtlp()`, updated `instrumentProject()` and `configureAgent()` Rust branches in `src/lib/otlp.ts` — no file overlap with this story\n   154→- 8-7 created `templates/otlp/rust.md` — no overlap\n   155→- 8-7 confirmed all tests pass with zero regressions\n   156→- This story touches `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` only — clean isolation from 8-7\n   157→\n   158→### Git Intelligence\n   159→\n   160→Recent commits: 2a601a7 (8-7 verified), f33294b (8-6 verified), 79f3449 (8-5 verified), 4e805b9 (8-4 verified), ebaddac (8-3 verified).\n   161→All previous Rust stories verified successfully. Pattern: single-module changes with focused tests.\n   162→\n   163→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   164→## Verification Requirements\n   165→\n   166→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding.proof.md`)\n   167→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   168→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   169→\n   170→## Documentation Requirements\n   171→\n   172→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   173→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding.md`\n   174→\n   175→## Testing Requirements\n   176→\n   177→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   178→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   179→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   180→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   181→\n   182→## Dev Agent Record\n   183→\n   184→### Agent Model Used\n   185→\n   186→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   187→\n   188→### Debug Log References\n   189→\n   190→N/A\n   191→\n   192→### Completion Notes List\n   193→\n   194→- Task 1: Added Cargo.toml `[package]` name parsing to `getProjectName()` as a fallback after package.json. Uses regex `/\\[package\\]([^[]*)/s` to isolate the `[package]` section, then `/^\\s*name\\s*=\\s*\"([^\"]+)\"/m` to extract the name. Wrapped in try/catch for graceful fallthrough. Added 13 lines to docs-scaffold.ts (now 220 lines, well under 300 NFR1 limit). No new dependencies (NFR3).\n   195→- Task 2: Verified existing Rust branches — `getStackLabel('rust')` returns `'Rust (Cargo.toml)'` (L35), `getCoverageTool('rust')` returns `'cargo-tarpaulin'` (L41), `generateAgentsMdContent(dir, 'rust')` includes `cargo build`, `cargo test`, `cargo tarpaulin --out json` (L75-82). All confirmed correct, no changes needed.\n   196→- Task 3: Added 4 new test cases: Cargo.toml-only project, package.json precedence over Cargo.toml, dependencies-only Cargo.toml fallback, malformed Cargo.toml fallback. All existing Rust tests (getStackLabel, getCoverageTool, generateAgentsMdContent) continue to pass.\n   197→- Task 4: Full test suite passes — 28 vitest docs-scaffold tests, 3018 total vitest tests across 113 files, 307 BATS integration tests. Zero regressions.\n   198→\n   199→### File List\n   200→\n   201→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Modified: added Cargo.toml parsing fallback in `getProjectName()`\n   202→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — Modified: added 4 new test cases for Cargo.toml project name extraction\n   203→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pjqm6RwzFUa1tNdjiqKz4j","session_id":"9c50fb69-0476-4a5d-8998-78fcdfa47c24","uuid":"6eed8050-0ae1-4a4f-919f-b1ec8a307b5b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:18:13.451Z"}
