{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pjqm6RwzFUa1tNdjiqKz4j","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 31 tests pass. \n\n---\n\n**Review Complete**\n\n**Story:** 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding\n**Story Status:** verifying\n**Issues Fixed:** 5 (3 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM)\n**Tests:** 31 passing (was 28, added 3 new tests)\n**Coverage:** 97.06% overall, all 123 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` -- Fixed Cargo.toml regex to handle section boundaries correctly and support single-quoted names\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` -- Fixed import ordering, made assertions more rigorous, added 3 new test cases\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/docs/exec-plans/active/8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding.proof.md` -- Created showboat proof document\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding.md` -- Status updated to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n\n- **HIGH-1:** Missing showboat proof document at `docs/exec-plans/active/8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding.proof.md`. Created.\n- **HIGH-2:** Cargo.toml name regex only matched double-quoted values (`\"name\"`), not single-quoted (`'name'`). Single quotes are valid TOML literal strings. Fixed regex to `[\"']([^\"']+)[\"']`.\n- **HIGH-3:** Cargo.toml section regex `([^[]*)` would break if a value contained `[` (e.g., `description = \"A [great] project\"`). Fixed to `([\\s\\S]*?)(?=\\n\\[|$)` which correctly stops at the next section header line.\n- **MEDIUM-1:** Test for `[dependencies]`-only Cargo.toml only asserted `not.toBe('dep-name')` without verifying the actual fallback value. Fixed to assert `toBe(basename(testDir))`.\n- **MEDIUM-2:** No test for `[package]` section with no `name` field. Added test case.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n\n- **LOW-1:** Import ordering of `afterEach` was at line 41 after its usage at line 37 (fixed as part of MEDIUM-3).\n- **LOW-2:** No test for empty Cargo.toml file (empty string). Covered implicitly by the \"malformed\" test, but a dedicated test would be marginally more explicit.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n\n- Lines 180, 221-222 in `docs-scaffold.ts` remain uncovered (the `docsScaffold = 'exists'` branch when `docs/` already exists, and the outer `catch` block in `scaffoldDocs`). These are pre-existing gaps unrelated to story 8-8 changes. The outer catch would require simulating an error during file generation which is difficult to trigger with the mock in place.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n\n- The mixed quote regex `[\"']([^\"']+)[\"']` does not enforce matching quotes (e.g., `name = \"foo'` would match). This is acceptable for a simple parser that explicitly avoids adding a TOML dependency (NFR3), and malformed TOML is not a realistic concern. Documenting as tech debt.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story proceeds to verification."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abf424cf2df062bf5 (use SendMessage with to: 'abf424cf2df062bf5' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 42928\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 212140</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c50fb69-0476-4a5d-8998-78fcdfa47c24","uuid":"177be425-9289-42c9-934b-8eface75a614","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:21:36.223Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any question