{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Cz6Gmr7CfLLqgB3SHZg5ph","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c50fb69-0476-4a5d-8998-78fcdfa47c24","uuid":"40d6a5e4-e75d-49ae-a302-f15bf84b57ac","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:21:51.218Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"No issues reported. All 28 docs-scaffold tests pass, 3018/3018 vitest tests pass, 307/307 BATS tests pass. Clean implementation.\n","newString":"No issues reported. All 28 docs-scaffold tests pass, 3018/3018 vitest tests pass, 307/307 BATS tests pass. Clean implementation.\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — code-review (2026-03-23T12:25Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Cargo.toml regex only matched double-quoted values.** Single quotes are valid TOML. Fixed to support both.\n- **HIGH: Cargo.toml section regex broke on `[` in values.** Fixed to use `[\\s\\S]*?` with lookahead for next section.\n- **HIGH: Missing showboat proof document.** Created.\n- **MEDIUM: Test assertion too weak** for dependencies-only Cargo.toml. Fixed to verify actual fallback value.\n- **MEDIUM: No test for `[package]` section with no `name` field.** Added.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Mixed quote regex doesn't enforce matching quotes** — acceptable for simple parser per NFR3.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Pre-existing uncovered lines 180, 221-222** in docs-scaffold.ts (unrelated to 8-8).\n","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 5)\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — create-story (2026-03-23T12:14Z)\n\n- **Observation: ACs 1-3 are already implemented.** Code for `getStackLabel('rust')`, `getCoverageTool('rust')`, and the Rust branch in `generateAgentsMdContent()` was added in earlier stories. Only AC4 (`getProjectName` Cargo.toml parsing) is new work.\n- **Risk: Cargo.toml parsing edge cases.** Simple regex parsing without a TOML parser could break on comments, inline tables, or multi-line strings. Known tradeoff per NFR4.\n- **Workaround: sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent.** Had to manually update status to `ready-for-dev`.\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — dev-story (2026-03-23T12:18Z)\n\nNo issues reported. All 28 docs-scaffold tests pass, 3018/3018 vitest tests pass, 307/307 BATS tests pass. Clean implementation.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":9,"oldLines":3,"newStart":9,"newLines":13,"lines":[" ### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — dev-story (2026-03-23T12:18Z)"," "," No issues reported. All 28 docs-scaffold tests pass, 3018/3018 vitest tests pass, 307/307 BATS tests pass. Clean implementation.","+","+### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — code-review (2026-03-23T12:25Z)","+","+- **HIGH: Cargo.toml regex only matched double-quoted values.** Single quotes are valid TOML. Fixed to support both.","+- **HIGH: Cargo.toml section regex broke on `[` in values.** Fixed to use `[\\s\\S]*?` with lookahead for next section.","+- **HIGH: Missing showboat proof document.** Created.","+- **MEDIUM: Test assertion too weak** for dependencies-only Cargo.toml. Fixed to verify actual fallback value.","+- **MEDIUM: No test for `[package]` section with no `name` field.** Added.","+- **LOW (not fixed): Mixed quote regex doesn't enforce matching quotes** — acceptable for simple parser per NFR3.","+- **LOW (not fixed): Pre-existing uncovered lines 180, 221-222** in docs-scaffold.ts (unrelated to 8-8)."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
