{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QW2GCFgz9epqRKXWoRCrWR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 5)\n     2→\n     3→### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — create-story (2026-03-23T12:14Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Observation: ACs 1-3 are already implemented.** Code for `getStackLabel('rust')`, `getCoverageTool('rust')`, and the Rust branch in `generateAgentsMdContent()` was added in earlier stories. Only AC4 (`getProjectName` Cargo.toml parsing) is new work.\n     6→- **Risk: Cargo.toml parsing edge cases.** Simple regex parsing without a TOML parser could break on comments, inline tables, or multi-line strings. Known tradeoff per NFR4.\n     7→- **Workaround: sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent.** Had to manually update status to `ready-for-dev`.\n     8→\n     9→### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — dev-story (2026-03-23T12:18Z)\n    10→\n    11→No issues reported. All 28 docs-scaffold tests pass, 3018/3018 vitest tests pass, 307/307 BATS tests pass. Clean implementation.\n    12→\n    13→### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — code-review (2026-03-23T12:25Z)\n    14→\n    15→- **HIGH: Cargo.toml regex only matched double-quoted values.** Single quotes are valid TOML. Fixed to support both.\n    16→- **HIGH: Cargo.toml section regex broke on `[` in values.** Fixed to use `[\\s\\S]*?` with lookahead for next section.\n    17→- **HIGH: Missing showboat proof document.** Created.\n    18→- **MEDIUM: Test assertion too weak** for dependencies-only Cargo.toml. Fixed to verify actual fallback value.\n    19→- **MEDIUM: No test for `[package]` section with no `name` field.** Added.\n    20→- **LOW (not fixed): Mixed quote regex doesn't enforce matching quotes** — acceptable for simple parser per NFR3.\n    21→- **LOW (not fixed): Pre-existing uncovered lines 180, 221-222** in docs-scaffold.ts (unrelated to 8-8).\n    22→\n    23→### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — verification (2026-03-23T12:30Z)\n    24→\n    25→- All 7 ACs passed. Verifier used a Node.js script (`verify-acs.mjs`) to import and test the functions directly from the dist bundle — creative approach.\n    26→- **OBSERVABILITY GAP on all ACs:** No log events detected for any of the docs-scaffold function calls. These are pure utility functions with no instrumentation — expected for documentation scaffolding.\n    27→- **AC7 indirect:** Test source files not shipped in npm package, so vitest/bats couldn't run in container. Verified indirectly via all 6 functional ACs passing + dev agent's test report.\n    28→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JvC5i6ygiD4DfosAy79dLU","session_id":"9c50fb69-0476-4a5d-8998-78fcdfa47c24","uuid":"affdbaf5-30ca-457f-9894-61ce23e1e85f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:29:40.257Z"}
